# XGBoosted Orchestrator

## Project Description

This project proposes to simplify the model deployment and monitoring workflow for the open-source [XGBoost](https://xgboost.readthedocs.io/en/stable/) library. Key features entail:

1. Realtime monitoring of model metrics
    
    Critical metrics of a model should be continuously presented to users via the terminal or browser. 

2. Logging & interval configuration

    Model events and metrics should be automatically logged to a persistent store. Access to logged information should be as simple and intuitive as possible.

3. Model configuration

    The parameters of the model should be able to configured via the terminal in an elegant way. 

4. Model project instantiation

    Workflows are abstracted into individual project instances which contain specified configurations and metadata. 


Object-oriented paradigms 

```python
class Status(Enum):
    Ok = True
    Err = False


class PredictionType(Enum):
    C = True
    R = False

class Metrics:
    def __init__(self, ptype: PredictionType)


class ProjectStore:
    def __init__(self):
        self.root: str

    def add(self, name: str) -> Status:
    def display(self) -> None:
    def rename(self, old_name: str, new_name: str) -> Status:
    def delete(self, name: str) -> Status:
    

class Project:
    def __init__(self, name: str, ptype: PredictionType):
        self.name: str = name
        self.path: str = 
        self.params: Dict = self._get_params()
        self.champion: str = self._get_champion()

    def train_xgb(self, model: str, params: Dict) -> None:
    def config_model(self, model: Model, params: Dict) -> None:
    def run(self, model: Model, data_path: str, mode: str = "default") -> None: 
    def delete_model(self, name: str) -> Status:

    def show(self) -> None:


class DataStore:
    def __init__(self): 
        self.path: str

    def add(self, name: str) -> Status:
    def show(self, name: str) -> None:
    def update(self, old_name: str, new_name: str) -> Status:
    def delete(self, name: str) -> Status:
    

class Model:
    def __init__(self, name: str):
        self.name: str = name
        self.params: Dict = self._get_model_params()
        self.model: xgb.XGBClassifier() | xgb.XGBRegressor()
        self.metrics: Dict = self._get_model_metrics()

    def show_metadata(self) -> None:
